'From Cuis7.9 [latest update: #8004] on 17 June 2026 at 1:45:18 pm'!
!Duration class methodsFor: 'squeak protocol' stamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026 13:26:08' prior: 16855172!
             fromString: aString
	"
	Folow ANSI 5.8.2.16. See Duration >> #readFrom:
	Format is DD:hh:mm:ss
	Duration fromString: '12:23:34:45'
	Duration fromString: '1:6:50:00'

	Extended to accept non-ANSI formats, such as:
			hh:mm:ss
			hh:mm
			+hh:mm:ss
			+hh:mm
			-hh:mm:ss
			-hh:mm
		Duration fromString: '1:50:00'
		Duration fromString: '5:30.5'
		Duration fromString: '01:00'
		Duration fromString: '+02:00'
		Duration fromString: '-03:00'
	and:
		Duration fromString: '3.5h'
		Duration fromString: '2.5min'
		Duration fromString: '1.5s'
		Duration fromString: '200s'
		Duration fromString: '200ms'
	"
	| colons fullFormat |

	"If aString includes at least one $:, complete ANSI format"
	colons := aString occurrencesOf: $:.
	colons > 0 ifTrue: [
		fullFormat := aString.
		aString first isDigit ifFalse: [ fullFormat := fullFormat copyFrom: 2 to: fullFormat size ].
		colons < 3 ifTrue: [ "Add zero days"
			fullFormat := '00:', fullFormat ].
		colons = 1 ifTrue: [ "Add zero seconds"
			fullFormat := fullFormat, ':00' ].
		aString first isDigit ifFalse: [ fullFormat := aString first asString, fullFormat ].
		^ self readFrom: fullFormat readStream ].

	"'3.5h' means 3.5 hours"
	(aString endsWith: 'h') ifTrue: [
		^self hours: aString asNumber ].

	"'3.5min' means 3.5 minutes"
	(aString endsWith: 'min') ifTrue: [
		^self minutes: aString asNumber ].

	"'3ms' means 3 milliseconds"
	(aString endsWith: 'ms') ifTrue: [
		^self milliSeconds: aString asNumber ].

	"'3.5s' means 3.5 seconds"
	(aString endsWith: 's') ifTrue: [
		^self seconds: aString asNumber ].

	^nil! !

----End fileIn of /Users/juanvuletich/Cuis-Smalltalk/Cuis-Smalltalk-Dev/CoreUpdates/8005-Duration-fromString-enh-JuanVuletich-2026Jun17-13h45m-jmv.001.cs.st----!

'From Cuis7.9 [latest update: #8004] on 17 June 2026 at 1:47:39 pm'!
!DateAndTime class methodsFor: 'squeak protocol' stamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026 13:16:55'!
                          date: aDate time: aTimeOrNil offset: anUTCoffset
	"If anOffset is nil, use local time zone.
	If UTC is desired, pass Duration zero as the offset."

	anUTCoffset ifNil: [
		^ self date: aDate time: aTimeOrNil ].

	aTimeOrNil ifNil: [
		^ self 
			year: aDate yearNumber
			day: aDate dayOfYear
			hour: 0
			minute: 0
			second: 0
			offset: anUTCoffset ].

	^ self 
		year: aDate yearNumber
		day: aDate dayOfYear
		hour: aTimeOrNil hour
		minute: aTimeOrNil minute
		second: aTimeOrNil second
		offset: anUTCoffset! !

----End fileIn of /Users/juanvuletich/Cuis-Smalltalk/Cuis-Smalltalk-Dev/CoreUpdates/8006-DateAndTime-creationWithUTCoffset-JuanVuletich-2026Jun17-13h45m-jmv.001.cs.st----!

'From Cuis7.9 [latest update: #8004] on 17 June 2026 at 2:24:51 pm'!
!CompiledMethod class methodsFor: 'services' stamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026 14:22:58' prior: 16838243!
      authorAndStamp: authorAndStamp partsDo: aBlock
	"Given a method time stamp string (see senders, see #authorAndStampAsSaved)
	evaluate a block on its parts: author initials[String] and timestamp[DateAndTime].
	Parts may be nil if not present.
	Support the various formats saved by Smalltalk-80, Squeak and Cuis over the years.
(Examples follow)
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'Squeak1.2 29/Jun/1997 10:40:55' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: ' 9/Jun/1997 00:00:00' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011 14:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 10/Jan/2014 22:53:00' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 am ' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 pm ' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 23:02:25' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 am (-03:00)' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25Z' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 UTC' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 (UTC)' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25UTC' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25(UTC)' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 am UTC' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 11:02:25 am (UTC)' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011T14:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011X14:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011 14:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011T4:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011X4:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5/20/2011 4:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
	CompiledMethod authorAndStamp: 'jmv 5-20-2011 4:37' partsDo: [ :initials :timestamp | {initials. timestamp} print ].
"
	| authorAndDateParts authorPart colonPosition authorDateSeparator timePart datePart utcOffsetPart utcOffset dateAndTime |
	authorAndStamp ifNil: [^aBlock value: nil value: nil].
	authorAndDateParts := authorAndStamp.

	"Look for a Time (perhaps with an UTC offset afterwards)"
	colonPosition := authorAndStamp indexOf: $:.
	colonPosition = 0 ifFalse: [ | dateEnd timeStart utcOffsetStart |
		timeStart := (authorAndStamp at: colonPosition-2) isDigit
			ifTrue: [colonPosition-2]
			ifFalse: [colonPosition-1].
		dateEnd := (authorAndStamp at: timeStart-2) isDigit
			ifTrue: [timeStart-2]
			ifFalse: [timeStart-3].
		timePart := authorAndStamp copyFrom: timeStart to: authorAndStamp size.
		authorAndDateParts := authorAndStamp copyFrom: 1 to: dateEnd.
		"Look for a final UTC offset"
		utcOffsetPart := nil.
		utcOffsetStart := timePart indexOf: $(.
		utcOffsetStart = 0
			ifFalse: [
				utcOffsetPart := timePart copyFrom: utcOffsetStart+1 to: timePart size-1.
				timePart := timePart copyFrom: 1 to: utcOffsetStart-1 ]
			ifTrue: [
				utcOffsetStart := timePart indexOf: $Z ifAbsent: [timePart indexOf: $U].
				utcOffsetStart = 0 ifFalse: [
					utcOffsetPart := timePart copyFrom: utcOffsetStart to: timePart size.
					timePart := timePart copyFrom: 1 to: utcOffsetStart-1 ]].
		utcOffset := utcOffsetPart ifNotNil: [
			(utcOffsetPart = 'UTC' or: [ utcOffsetPart = 'Z'])
				ifTrue: [Duration zero]
				ifFalse: [Duration fromString: utcOffsetPart ]]].

	"Look for a Date. Separate authorPart and datePart."
	authorDateSeparator := authorAndDateParts lastIndexOf: Character space.
	datePart := authorAndDateParts copyFrom: authorDateSeparator+1 to: authorAndDateParts size.
	((datePart occurrencesOf: $/) >=2 or: [ (datePart occurrencesOf: $-) >=2  ])
		ifTrue: [
			authorPart := authorDateSeparator > 0 ifTrue: [authorAndDateParts copyFrom: 1 to: authorDateSeparator] ifFalse: ['unknown']]
		ifFalse: [
			authorPart := authorAndDateParts.
			datePart := nil.].

	dateAndTime := datePart ifNotNil: [
		DateAndTime
			date: (Date fromString: datePart)
			time: (timePart ifNotNil: [Time fromString: timePart withBlanksTrimmed])
			offset: utcOffset ].
	^aBlock
		value: authorPart withBlanksTrimmed
		value: dateAndTime! !

----End fileIn of /Users/juanvuletich/Cuis-Smalltalk/Cuis-Smalltalk-Dev/CoreUpdates/8007-methodStamp-broaderFormatSupport-JuanVuletich-2026Jun17-13h47m-jmv.001.cs.st----!

'From Cuis7.9 [latest update: #8004] on 17 June 2026 at 2:32:00 pm'!
!Utilities class methodsFor: 'identification' stamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026 00:17:59' prior: 17014143!
                          changeStamp
	"Answer a string to be pasted into source code to mark who changed it and when.
	Utilities changeStamp
	'jmv 16/Jun/2026, 9:01:18 pm (UTC)' .
	'jmv 16/Jun/2026 17:20:43' .
	"
	"^ self authorInitials , ' ' , (Date today printFormat: #(1 2 3 $/ 2 1)), ' ',
		(String streamContents: [:s | Time now print24: true showSeconds: true on: s]).
		"
	^String streamContents: [ :strm |
		strm nextPutAll: self authorInitials.
		strm space.
		DateAndTime nowUTC printNiceOn: strm ]! !

----End fileIn of /Users/juanvuletich/Cuis-Smalltalk/Cuis-Smalltalk-Dev/CoreUpdates/8008-changeStamp-nicerFormat-JuanVuletich-2026Jun17-14h24m-jmv.001.cs.st----!

'From Cuis7.9 [latest update: #8004] on 17 June 2026 at 2:33:25 pm'!
!CompiledMethod methodsFor: 'time stamp' stamp: 'jmv 17/Jun/2026, 12:16:57 am (UTC)' prior: 16837810!
          authorAndStamp
	"Answer the authoring time-stamp for the given method, retrieved from the sources or changes file.
	Answer the empty string if no time stamp is available.
	Format the date in the timestamp with the preferred style.
	(Object compiledMethodAt: #printString) authorAndStampAsSaved
	(Object compiledMethodAt: #printString) authorAndStamp
	"
	| asSaved |
	asSaved := self authorAndStampAsSaved.
	asSaved isEmpty ifTrue: [ ^asSaved ].
	^String streamContents: [ :strm | 
		self class authorAndStamp: asSaved partsDo: [ :authorInitials :dateAndTime |
			strm nextPutAll: authorInitials.
			strm space.
			dateAndTime asUTC printNiceOn: strm ]]! !

----End fileIn of /Users/juanvuletich/Cuis-Smalltalk/Cuis-Smalltalk-Dev/CoreUpdates/8009-NicerMethodStampFormat-JuanVuletich-2026Jun17-14h32m-jmv.001.cs.st----!

